          "CanopyType": null,
          "Name": "CLEM",
          "ResourceName": null,
          "Children": [
            {
              "$type": "Models.Memo, Models",
              "Text": "# Notes\n## Pasture\n* The Field is provided from the AgPasture example\n* This paddock is linked to the CLEM GrazeFoodStore by a GrazeFoodStoreAPSIMLink which CLEM can then treat as a pasture\n* No rotation or animal movelemt is applied in this simulation.\n\n## Herd\n* The new GrowPF anaimal production sub-model is used.\n  * The previous Grow component is also provided but disabled.\n* The max number of breeders in Activities\\ManageHerd\\Manage numbers will set the herd size with the initial cohorts scaled to this number\n* Breeders will be provided from heifers or purchased up to max breeders as needed in the Manage numbers activity\n* The herd will graze the paddock in which they are located\n* Hay is fed to fill any potential intake shortfall from grazing\n* Controlled mating is performed from January to May\n  * No bulls are required in the herd for controlled mating and have been omitted.\n  * Any female over 0.85 relative condition will conceive at mating (prob of conceiving = 1.0)\n* Weaning occurs in any month where suckling are at least 4 months old or 100kg.\n* Old breeders will be sold at 10 years old regardless of pregnancy or lactation status\n  * This will occur in the Manage number activitiy based on its timer\n\n## Initial simulation setup\n* Breeding turned off (Activity disabled)\n* Weaning turned off (Activity disabled as not needed as no sucklings in initial herd and not doing breeding)\n* Represents a breeder herd close to Maximum number of breeders.\n* Mortality is not included so breeders will persist until age at sale\n  * Breeders may fall to unrealistic body condition \n  * This is left to identify the ability of the pasture and management rules to support the numbers supplied\n\n\n",
              "Name": "Memo",
              "ResourceName": null,
              "Children": [],
              "Enabled": true,
              "ReadOnly": false
            },
